FBIS3-29932 "dreas037_c_94017" FBIS-EAS-94-037 Document Type:Daily Report 24 Feb 1994 North Korea Envoy to Kazakhstan Bids Farewell to Party Chief SK2302024494 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean 1500 GMT 15 Feb 94 SK2302024494 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean 1500 GMT 15 Feb 94 Language: Korean Article Type:BFN [Summary] Pak Chae-pil, our ambassador to Kazakhstan, paid a farewell visit to Svoik, cochairman of the Kazakh Socialist Party, on 11 February. During the meeting, the cochairman asked the ambassador to convey his greetings to Kim Il-song and Kim Chong-il. He said that his party cherishes relations with the Workers' Party of Korea and that he supports the DPRK position of resolving the nuclear issue on the Korean peninsula through DPRK-U.S. talks.
